On 7/30/04 2:53 PM, "Phil Cappellini" <philcappellini(-at-)hotmail.com> wrote:

> I am about to replace the front shift rod bush. I have disconnected the
> shifter, the coupling (underneath the van) and removed the rubber boot at
> the entrance of the tube that the rod travels through to get to the tranny.

By front you meant the front of the rear shift rod?
 
> When I removed the boot I did not see the old bushing, maybe it has fallen
> apart and gone further back?. How far back should the bushing go from the
> entrance of the tube? Can I slide the new bushing on and push it as far back
> as I can, will this work?

You will need to disconnect the shift coupler at the nose cone and push the
rear shift rod forward to reveal the frontmost bushing.

